issues.description: The constructor signature in the solution does not follow the parameter order specified in the problem statement UML. The exercise instructs to initialize attributes in the order lectureName, numberOfInscribedStudents, numberOfGuestStudents, numberOfLecturers, numberOfTutors, but the solution implements the constructor parameters as (String lectureName, int numberOfLecturers, int numberOfTutors, int numberOfInscribedStudents, int numberOfGuestStudents). This mismatch will confuse students and cause constructor tests to fail.
issues.suggested_fix: Change the constructor in Lecture.java to match the UML order: public Lecture(String lectureName, int numberOfInscribedStudents, int numberOfGuestStudents, int numberOfLecturers, int numberOfTutors) {...}
